It's impossible to write an object allocation expression (e.g., `new C()`)
on the left-hand side of a method invocation (e.g., `new Point().toString()`)
or field access (e.g., `new Point().a`).

frontmatter.shortDescription: Method calls or field accesses cannot be chained to a constructor invocation
frontmatter.shortCorrection: Method calls or field accesses can be chained to a constructor invocation
